# Copy-Sync Customization Workflow

## How the System Works

`rhdh-customizations/` is the single source of truth for all configuration customizations. The `apply-customizations.sh` script **copies** these files into `rhdh-local/` so containers can read them from their expected mounted paths. After editing any customization file, you must re-run this script to sync.

## File Mapping

Source (in `rhdh-customizations/`) --> Destination (copied to `rhdh-local/`):

- `compose.override.yaml` --> `compose.override.yaml` (Compose overrides: extra services, extra_hosts)
- `.env` --> `.env` (Environment variable overrides)
- `configs/app-config/app-config.local.yaml` --> `configs/app-config/app-config.local.yaml` (App config overrides)
- `configs/dynamic-plugins/dynamic-plugins.override.yaml` --> `configs/dynamic-plugins/dynamic-plugins.override.yaml` (Plugin overrides)
- `developer-lightspeed/configs/app-config/app-config.lightspeed.local.yaml` --> `developer-lightspeed/configs/app-config/app-config.lightspeed.local.yaml` (Lightspeed config)
- `configs/catalog-entities/*.override.yaml` --> `configs/catalog-entities/*.override.yaml` (Catalog entity overrides, e.g. custom users for GitHub auth)
- `configs/extra-files/*` --> `configs/extra-files/*` (Additional config, e.g. github-app-credentials.yaml)

## File Purposes

- `.env` -- Environment variables (overrides `rhdh-local/default.env`)
- `compose.override.yaml` -- Docker Compose services, ports, volumes, extra_hosts
- `configs/app-config/app-config.local.yaml` -- RHDH application configuration
- `configs/dynamic-plugins/dynamic-plugins.override.yaml` -- Plugin enablement and configuration
- `developer-lightspeed/configs/app-config/app-config.lightspeed.local.yaml` -- Lightspeed AI assistant config
- `configs/extra-files/github-app-credentials.yaml` -- GitHub App authentication credentials

## Configuration Layers

- **Layer 1 (Defaults)**: `rhdh-local/` version-controlled files (`default.env`, `app-config.yaml`, `dynamic-plugins.default.yaml`)
- **Layer 2 (Overrides)**: Files copied from `rhdh-customizations/` (`.env`, `app-config.local.yaml`, `dynamic-plugins.override.yaml`)
- **Layer 3 (Examples)**: `*.example.yaml` templates in `rhdh-local/` for reference

## The Standard Workflow

```bash
# 1. Edit customizations (always in rhdh-customizations/)
code rhdh-customizations/configs/app-config/app-config.local.yaml

# 2. Sync copies into rhdh-local
cd rhdh-customizations && ./apply-customizations.sh

# 3. Restart containers using scripts
cd .. && ./down.sh && ./up.sh --customized --both --ollama
```

## Configuration Examples

### Environment Variables

```bash
# Override default values by setting them in .env
# Don't modify rhdh-local/default.env
RHDH_IMAGE=quay.io/rhdh-community/rhdh:latest
LOG_LEVEL=debug
```

### Plugin Configuration

```yaml
# In dynamic-plugins.override.yaml:
includes:
  - dynamic-plugins.default.yaml  # Load defaults first

plugins:
  - package: ./local-plugins/my-plugin
    disabled: false
```

### App Configuration

```yaml
# In app-config.local.yaml, override specific values:
backend:
  database:
    connection:
      host: postgres
      port: 5432
```

## NEVER Do This

- Modify files directly in `rhdh-local/` for customization purposes
- Manually copy files from `rhdh-customizations/` into `rhdh-local/` (use `apply-customizations.sh`)
- Commit files matching: `*.local.yaml`, `*.override.yaml`, `.env` to the rhdh-local repository
- Edit the copied customization files in `rhdh-local/` (edit the source in `rhdh-customizations/` instead)
- Suggest editing default configurations in `rhdh-local/` for user customization

## ALWAYS Do This

- Edit customization files in `rhdh-customizations/` directory
- Run `apply-customizations.sh` after every edit to sync copies
- Run `remove-customizations.sh` to test pristine state
- Respect `.gitignore` patterns in `rhdh-local/.gitignore`
- Verify pristine state: `cd rhdh-local && git status` shows "working tree clean"

## Important Notes

- Never commit `*.local.yaml`, `*.override.yaml`, or `.env` to the `rhdh-local` repository (they're gitignored there)
- These files can be version controlled independently in `rhdh-customizations/`
- Use `backup.sh` to create portable archives of your customizations
- The `remove-customizations.sh` script removes copies from `rhdh-local/` but never touches source files here
- Scripts: `apply-customizations.sh` and `remove-customizations.sh` are the ONLY way to manage customizations in `rhdh-local/`

## Configuration Change Quick Reference

What to edit and where:

- **App config**: `rhdh-customizations/configs/app-config/app-config.local.yaml`
- **Plugins**: `rhdh-customizations/configs/dynamic-plugins/dynamic-plugins.override.yaml`
- **Environment**: `rhdh-customizations/.env`
- **Compose services**: `rhdh-customizations/compose.override.yaml`
- **Lightspeed config**: `rhdh-customizations/developer-lightspeed/configs/app-config/app-config.lightspeed.local.yaml`
- **Credentials**: `rhdh-customizations/configs/extra-files/github-app-credentials.yaml`

All changes require: `apply-customizations.sh` --> `./down.sh` --> `./up.sh --customized [flags]`

## Git and Version Control

- `rhdh-local/` must always show clean git status (customization copies are gitignored)
- `rhdh-customizations/` can optionally be version controlled independently
- Update from upstream: `./down.sh` --> `cd rhdh-local && git pull` --> `cd ../rhdh-customizations && ./apply-customizations.sh` --> `cd .. && ./up.sh --customized [flags]`
